Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "svideti" in different forms and positions:

1. *Sviđa mi se* ova nova haljina. (I like this new dress.)
2. Ona *mi se sviđa*. (I like her.)
3. *Sviđate mi se* zbog svog smisla za humor. (I like you for your sense of humor.)
4. Kako ti se *ne sviđa* ova pesma? (How can you not like this song?)
5. *Ne sviđa mi se* tvoj stav prema tome. (I don't like your attitude towards that.)
6. *Sviđaju mi se* ove boje na zidu. (I like these colors on the wall.)
7. *Sviđa li ti se* ovaj restoran? (Do you like this restaurant?)
8. *Sviđa mi se* ideja da idemo na izlet. (I like the idea of going on a trip.)
9. *Sviđao mi se* taj film kad sam ga gledao prvi put. (I liked that movie when I watched it for the first time.)
10. Da li se *svidelo* deci na rođendanskoj zabavi? (Did the kids like the birthday party?)

I hope this helps!